The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 5: Jet Airways will cut fuel surcharge across all domestic sectors by Rs 400 from tomorrow, but there will be no reduction in basic fares. Following in the footsteps of Air India, Jet Airways and its wholly owned subsidiary JetLite will drop fuel surcharge. Jet will levy a surcharge of Rs 1,950 for a distance of less than 750 km and Rs 2,700 for distances beyond that.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 5: Business process outsourcing firms are likely to see 2.5 lakh job losses by the first quarter of 2009 in the wake of the downturn in the US and other developed economies, the Business Process Outsourcing Association of India said.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 5: The government will borrow another Rs 45,000 crore through bonds in the remaining part of this fiscal to meet additional expenditure following the approval of supplementary demand for grants by Parliament.                             
	 Jamshedpur, Dec. 5: Tata Motors Jamshedpur plant will remain closed for six days from December 8 to avoid piling up of inventories because of a slump in the demand.                            
	 Mumbai, Dec. 5: The RBI has formulated draft guidelines for change in management or takeover of firms by asset reconstruction companies, in case of willful default.                                                                                                                         
